  "evidence_entities": [
    {
      "id": "paper_id:introduction:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "intro_1",
      "text": "Synthetic lethality (SL) defines a type of genetic interaction where the co-occurrence of two (or more) genetic events results in cellular death, while the occurrence of either event on its own is compatible with cell viability",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:introduction:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "intro_2",
      "text": "This strategy has driven the development of sophisticated targeted therapies in cancer, such as PARP inhibitors for patients with BRCA1- or BRCA2-mutated breast cancer",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:introduction:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "intro_3",
      "text": "A promising related concept is synthetic dosage lethality (SDL), which defines a genetic interaction where the overexpression of a gene combined with the under-expression of a second gene leads to cellular death",
      "confidence": 0.95,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:1:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "results_1",
      "text": "Among different candidates, we identified the essentiality of EZH2 specifically in hematological cancer cell lines in all iMR models build on TRRUST. Interestingly, this gene has been previously identified as a drug target of different hematological tumors",
      "confidence": 0.9,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:2:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "results_2",
      "text": "Here, the lethality of EZH2 inhibition is mediated by the following gMIS: {EZH2\u2212, JUN\u2212, RELA+}, hypothesizing a higher impact in cellular proliferation when the expression of JUN is down-regulated and RELA is up-regulated",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:3:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "results_3",
      "text": "For illustration, consider the SDL interaction formed by the following two genes: {DUSP4+; GADD45B\u2212}, where the high expression of DUSP4 and the low expression of GADD45B inhibit cellular proliferation",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    },
    {
      "id": "paper_id:results:4:llm",
      "class": "Evidence",
      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "results_4",
      "text": "We also examined the following tumor suppressor gene complex comprising two genes: {CDK5RAP3+; SHC1+}, where the high expression of both genes is required to block cellular proliferation",
      "confidence": 0.85,
      "extraction_method": "llm",
      "study_type": "computational study",
      "eco_type": null,
      "source": "extracted"
    }
  ],
